# 🚪 Automatic Door Control System using STM32 (Ultrasonic + Servo)

## 📌 Overview

This project implements an **automatic door control system** using an ultrasonic sensor (HC-SR04) and a servo motor with an STM32 microcontroller. The system detects the presence of a person/object within a predefined distance and automatically opens and closes the door.

---

## 🎯 Features

* Contactless door operation
* Real-time distance measurement
* Automatic open/close mechanism
* Servo motor control using PWM
* Microsecond precision timing using hardware timer

---

## 🧠 Working Principle

The ultrasonic sensor continuously measures the distance to nearby objects. When an object is detected within a threshold distance (e.g., 20 cm), the system:

1. Opens the door (servo rotates)
2. Waits until the object moves away
3. Closes the door automatically

This ensures smooth and realistic automatic door behavior.

---

## 🔧 Hardware Used

* STM32 (e.g., STM32F446RE / Nucleo board)
* HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Sensor
* Servo Motor

---

## 🔌 Pin Configuration

| Peripheral | Pin            |
| ---------- | -------------- |
| TRIG       | PB5            |
| ECHO       | PA8            |
| Servo PWM  | PC7 (TIM3 CH2) |

---

## ⚙️ Software Configuration

* IDE: STM32CubeIDE
* Language: C (HAL Drivers)
* Timer 2 → Microsecond delay (1 MHz)
* Timer 3 → PWM (50 Hz for servo)

---

## 📏 Distance Calculation

```id="dcalc01"
distance (cm) = (time_us × 0.0343) / 2
```

---

## 🔄 System Logic

```id="flow01"
Read Distance → Check Threshold → Open Door → Wait → Close Door
```

---

## ▶️ How to Run

1. Open project in STM32CubeIDE
2. Build and flash the code
3. Place object within ~20 cm
4. Observe door opening and closing

---

## ⚠️ Notes

* Ensure stable **5V supply for servo motor**
* Ultrasonic sensor must be properly aligned
* Use common ground for all components
* Threshold distance can be modified in code

---

